00_Black

Rex was the very salvation for Alicia. He was the person who
made her dream of saving someone come true. He was the
person who made her dream of helping someone come true.

Rex was no longer just a mere bodyguard. It was the first
time that Alicia, who had become a torturer without knowing
love or affection, felt the sprouting of emotions. Without
knowing the name of this emotion, she was drawn to Rex.

Rex was the same. He was raised in the palace and knew of
love, but he didn't know about romantic love. He, too, was
drawn to Alicia, guided by an unnamed emotion.

For the two of them, the escape was a delayed youth. Alicia
remembered how colorful the world could be. There was
someone with whom she could talk about and share that
beauty.

It didn't take long for the two of them to become lovers. It
was a childish, make-believe kind of love that made the
adults scoff. It was a platonic relationship without carnal
desires that filled their hearts.

However, when the two of them were about to meet up with
their comrades near Oros, an incident occurred. Alicia and
the others were attacked due to a betrayal that was
reported. And then, a third party appeared during the
battle.

Rex was forcibly stuffed into the carriage by the third
party. In that moment, Alicia, filled with despair, grabbed
onto the hand that was dragging her in. It was a hand
wearing distinctive green clothing, belonging to multiple
individuals.

Alicia, relying only on that, would wander throughout the
empire. While worrying about Prince Rex's safety, she would
once again grip the wine.

There were actually three factions trying to reclaim Rex.
Queen Caron and her allies who wanted to capture the escaped
Rex. The faction of princes who wanted to assist in his
escape and make Prince Rex the king.

And so, the adventurer's guild, requested by Senator Pilia,
decided to get involved. Guild Master Agonia initially had
no intention of getting involved, but he decided to respond
to the heartfelt desire to help his nephew.

After that, Rex was hidden within the Adventurer's Guild.
And then, in exchange for Alicia, he left the Adventurer's
Guild and headed towards the stronghold of the prince's
faction built in Oros.
